#### Guessing Strategies for the ASVAB
Background context: Even though efficient studying is ideal, there might be times when you encounter questions that seem too difficult. Knowing how to make educated guesses can help maximize your score.

:p How can one make an educated guess on a multiple-choice question if they are unsure of the answer?
??x
To make an educated guess, look for clues within the question and among the options. Eliminate obviously incorrect answers first. If you’re still unsure, consider the process of elimination to narrow down your choices.

```java
// Pseudocode for guessing strategy
public class GuessingStrategy {
    String findBestGuess(List<String> options) {
        // Eliminate clearly wrong answers
        List<String> possibleAnswers = new ArrayList<>();
        for (String option : options) {
            if (!isOptionIncorrect(option)) {
                possibleAnswers.add(option);
            }
        }

        // Return a random or educated guess from remaining options
        return possibleAnswers.get((int)(Math.random() * possibleAnswers.size()));
    }

    boolean isOptionIncorrect(String option) {
        // Logic to determine if an option is incorrect based on context
        return false;  // Example placeholder
    }
}
```
