#### PiCAT Test Overview
Background context: The Pre-screening, internet-delivered Computer Adaptive Test (PiCAT) is designed for efficiency and speed in the enlistment process. It allows recruits to take a full-length ASVAB on any computer using an access code provided by recruiters.

:p What is the purpose of the PiCAT?
??x
The primary purpose of the PiCAT is to streamline the military recruitment process. By taking the test online, it helps speed up the initial screening stage and reduces the need for in-person verification testing at Military Entrance Processing Stations (MEPS).

Verification testing ensures that recruits have not cheated by comparing their PiCAT scores with those from a follow-up, proctored ASVAB at MEPS.

Code example for accessing PiCAT:
```java
// Pseudocode to access and take the PiCAT test
void accessPiCatTest(String accessCode) {
    // Logic to authenticate and start taking the PiCAT test
    System.out.println("Accessing PiCAT with code: " + accessCode);
}
```
