#### Paper-and-Pencil (P&P) ASVAB Disadvantages
Background context: While the P&P version of the ASVAB offers some advantages, it also has several drawbacks. Harder questions are randomly mixed with easier ones, which can lead to spending too much time on difficult questions and missing out on simpler ones.

:p What is a disadvantage of the paper-and-pencil version of the ASVAB?
??x
A significant disadvantage is that harder questions are interspersed with easier ones, potentially leading to a scenario where test-takers spend too much time trying to solve complex problems. This can result in not having enough time to answer simpler questions at the end of each subtest, thus lowering overall scores.

Code example for handling mixed difficulty:
```java
// Pseudocode to manage difficult and easy questions
void handleQuestion(int difficultyLevel) {
    if (difficultyLevel > 5) { // Assuming 1 is easy, 6 is hard
        System.out.println("Spending extra time on a challenging question.");
    } else {
        System.out.println("Quickly moving to an easier question.");
    }
}
```
