#### Important Subtests for Military Eligibility

Background context: The ASVAB test has a portion called the AFQT, which includes four subtests that are critical for military eligibility. These subtests—Word Knowledge, Paragraph Comprehension, Arithmetic Reasoning, and Mathematics Knowledge—are crucial to determine if you meet the minimum requirements to join the military.

:p Which subtests are most important in determining military eligibility?

??x
The most important subtests in determining military eligibility are Word Knowledge, Paragraph Comprehension, Arithmetic Reasoning, and Mathematics Knowledge. These four subtests form part of the AFQT score, which is used to decide if you meet the minimum requirements to enlist in the military.

```java
public class EligibilityCheck {
    public void checkEligibility() {
        int wordKnowledgeScore = 70; // Example score
        int paragraphComprehensionScore = 85; // Example score
        int arithmeticReasoningScore = 60; // Example score
        int mathematicsKnowledgeScore = 90; // Example score

        boolean eligible = (wordKnowledgeScore >= 40 && 
                            paragraphComprehensionScore >= 50 &&
                            arithmeticReasoningScore >= 31 &&
                            mathematicsKnowledgeScore >= 42);

        if (eligible) {
            System.out.println("You are eligible to enlist in the military.");
        } else {
            System.out.println("You need to focus on improving your scores in some subtests.");
        }
    }
}
```
